cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with computational geometry and algorithms for computing the directed Hausdorff distance between imprecise point sets in the plane. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and complexity theory, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of approximation algorithms and the mention of NP-hardness indicates that it could also be classified under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
